english:
  title: Inscription for the Conferral of Posthumous Title Upon the Holy Mother, Queen Regent of Korean Heritage
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In all of ritual and propriety, none stands greater than the rectification of names. In all filial devotion, none weighs heavier than repaying the debt owed to those who gave us life. And so we now follow the ancient rite of composing this proclamation, and humbly undertake the ceremony of bestowing a posthumous name.

    With reverent contemplation, I consider our Holy Mother of the Han clan—her character graced with celestial harmony, her virtue aligned with the yielding grace of earth itself. She illuminated the very root of human relations, and so dwelt forever in auspicious fortune. She steadied the foundations of kingly virtue, and thus ensured the flourishing of our line. Yet because the succession remained unresolved, a shadow fell upon her rank and station.

    Reflecting upon this, I, an humble man of mediocre talent, have come to receive this great mandate. That I was able to quell the rebellion born of disputed claims—what other hand guided this but the subtle spirits of heaven? By their grace alone have we reached this moment.

    Therefore, choosing an auspicious day, we present these modest offerings. It is fitting to bestow upon her a great and luminous title, that her brilliant virtue might be known to all. Thus do we send forth our appointed emissary to formally present this decree: We confer upon her the posthumous name of the Spiritually Wise.

    May the luminous heavens gaze down with compassion upon our earnest hearts. May the blessings thus granted illuminate the path of our descendants, bringing them eternal prosperity.
  footnotes:
    - The 'Holy Mother' (聖母) refers to the mother of King Sejo of Joseon, whose disputed succession Lee Cham helped to secure.
    - The rectification of names (正名) is a Confucian concept emphasizing proper titles and hierarchical distinctions as foundational to social order.
    - The 'rebellion born of disputed claims' (奪嫡之亂) alludes to the succession struggles that preceded Sejo's reign.
